data.Name: Cleantech Open
data.About:
Since 2005 Cleantech Open (CTO) has trained over 1200 early-stage clean technology startup entrepreneurs through its annual business accelerator. A majority of CTO alumni have survived the merciless technology startup "valley of death" and gone on to raise $1.2 billion and create over 3,000 clean economy jobs.

CTO's one-of-a-kind innovation ecosystem built over the last 11 years of programming spans key cleantech innovation hubs in the U.S. and globally. As a non-profit organization run largely by volunteers, there are many ways to contribute. Join our global network of innovation and together let's forge a clean and sustainable future.
data.Tagline: The Cleantech Open runs the world's largest cleantech accelerator.

data.Name: Climate KIC
data.About:
Keeping global temperature rise below 2˚C necessitates unprecedented change: new social dynamics, ways of doing business, capital flows, policymaking, economic models, and new ways of living. No one organisation can solve climate change on its own.

We catalyse the rapid innovation needed across sectors by convening the brightest minds to tackle challenges, empowering leaders through capacity building, and seed funding the most promising climate-positive businesses.

data.Name: Elemental Excelerator
data.About:
Elemental Excelerator helps startups change the world, one community at a time. Each year, we find 15-20 companies that best fit our mission and fund each company up to $1 million to improve systems that impact people’s lives: energy, transportation, water, agriculture, and beyond. What makes us unique? We co-fund, co-design, and co-develop projects and strategies that improve infrastructure and sustainably enhance communities.

We believe in the power of innovation and people to create transformative change. We work to improve communities through technology innovation, economic opportunity, and sustainable modernization. This is what we call place-based innovation. What does that mean? It means that we look at the challenges of a specific place and then work with the community and startups to solve these challenges in innovative ways.
data.Tagline: Elemental Excelerator helps startups change the world, one community at a time.

data.Name: Radicle Growth
data.About:
In our latest Radicle Challenge, we’ve teamed up with Syngenta, a leading agriculture company helping to improve global food security sustainably, to invest in two technology companies that are transforming the future of protein. This could include new protein sources, new protein conversion technologies, or improvements to existing protein systems. Consumers globally are demanding more protein and are looking for new sources of that protein.

A $1m investment will be made in the Challenge winner and a $250k investment to the second-place winner (in addition to a custom acceleration program and access to Radicle and Syngenta’s global ag networks). The global applicant pool will be narrowed to 4-6 finalists who will participate in a Pitch Day event this Fall with our panel of judges, including Erik Fyrwald, CEO of Syngenta, and Kirk Haney, Managing Partner of Radicle Growth.

Applications open on Tuesday, April 28 and will be accepted from companies of all stages, all around the world.
data.Tagline: Radicle Growth is a San Diego, Calif.-based accelerator and venture capital firm.
